                            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=wesmckinn&avatarId=29931"
                        },
                        "displayName": "Wes McKinney",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "America/New_York"
                    },
                    "body": "I talked this proposal through with Julien yesterday and we should be able to manage without additional metadata by treating the contiguous buffer block written as part of the file format as a \"memory page\" for the purposes of record batch reconstruction -- so we will not consider the offset from the beginning of the physical file to be semantically meaningful. This is distinct from the shared memory IPC case where the buffers may occur in many different places in one or more shared memory regions. \n\nI'll write up some details under format/ about this more precisely in the course of implementing this in my patch for ARROW-363. ",
